received her appeal, though it stressed that her chances of immediate relief remain slim.\", \"from\": 456, \"to\": 612, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The Court\", \"from\": 456, \"to\": 465}, {\"ngram\": \"Arbitration\", \"from\": 469, \"to\": 480}, {\"ngram\": \"Sport\", \"from\": 485, \"to\": 490}, {\"ngram\": \"CAS)announcedon\", \"from\": 492, \"to\": 507}, {\"ngram\": \"her appeal\", \"from\": 532, \"to\": 542}, {\"ngram\": \"her chances\", \"from\": 568, \"to\": 579}, {\"ngram\": \"immediate relief\", \"from\": 583, \"to\": 599}]}, {\"sentence\": \"At the center of the dispute is World Boxing's requirement that female athletes undergo chromosomal testing before competing.\", \"from\": 614, \"to\": 739, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 652, \"end\": 658, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Boxing\", \"score\": 0.9999798391370013, \"rank\": 2.004741344398619e-05, \"text\": \"Boxing\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Boxing\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Boxing\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the center\", \"from\": 617, \"to\": 627}, {\"ngram\": \"the dispute\", \"from\": 631, \"to\": 642}, {\"ngram\": \"female athletes\", \"from\": 678, \"to\": 693}, {\"ngram\": \"chromosomal testing\", \"from\": 702, \"to\": 721}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Khelif rejects this rule, arguing it unfairly prevents her from taking part in international tournaments.\", \"from\": 740, \"to\": 845, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Khelif\", \"from\": 740, \"to\": 746}, {\"ngram\": \"this rule\", \"from\": 755, \"to\": 764}, {\"ngram\": \"part\", \"from\": 811, \"to\": 815}, {\"ngram\": \"international tournaments\", \"from\": 819, \"to\": 844}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The regulation already forced her to miss the Eindhoven competition in June, and she now asks to be allowed to enter the upcoming World Championships in Liverpool without the test.\", \"from\": 847, \"to\": 1027, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 893, \"end